						<summary>

						<p>Stone slab at the near entrance of the Rāmasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to mention Kōki. • • • Probably the donor and • • • • • rēbōḷu, the donee. Also records a gift of land as <hi rend="italic">pannasa.</hi> The details of the gift are lost. In characters of the 9th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
